    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="360"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d360">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Lord
                        Lyons</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Lord</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge with much
                    satisfaction the receipt of your communication of the 22d ultimo, relative to
                    the case of the schooner J. L. Gerety, or Eureka.</p>
                <p>Thanking your lordship for the information it contains, I have the honor to be,
                    with high consideration, my lord, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Right Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">Lord Lyons</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
